parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including loss of dashboard gauges, headlights, and other essential systems, which can lead to accidents, inconvenience, and safety risks.
symptoms: Dashboard gauges (speedometer
odometer
gas gauge
temperature gauge
RPM meter) not working or malfunctioning
headlights and taillights not functioning
dim or no headlights
cruise control light staying on
door light remaining on
horn malfunctioning
smoke or fire in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of headlights and taillights can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions, as other drivers may not be able to see the vehicle.
symptoms: Headlights and taillights not functioning
dim or no headlights
loss of parking lights
failure of dashboard lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause starting issues, which can lead to inconvenience and safety risks, and in extreme cases, electrical fires that can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: Difficulty starting the vehicle
clicking sounds from the engine compartment
smoke or fire in the engine compartment.

symptoms: The vehicle loses steering power
the vehicle drifts off course
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering feels heavy or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes lock up when pressed
the brakes have more power than expected
the vehicle is difficult to slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual noise can be a sign of a underlying issue that may lead to a loss of vehicle control or other safety concerns.
symptoms: A fine sound is heard when driving at a certain speed (e.g. 55 mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering alignment issues can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, leading to uneven tire wear and potentially affecting vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle needs frequent steering alignment
the tires wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The trunk closure issues can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety concerns if the trunk is not properly secured.

the trunk needs to be slammed shut.
